{{Wireless embedded system |brand=TRENDnet |model=TEW-639GR |revision=V3.0R |upc= |ean= |asin= |price= |est_release_date= |fcc_date=05/18/2011 |manuf_country=Taiwan |manuf=U-MEDIA |manuf_model=WRT-391R |manuf_rev= |availability= |type=wireless router |fcc_id=XU8TEW639GRV3 |ic_id= |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=0.5 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Realtek |cpu1_model=RTL8198 |cpu1_cspeed=620 |fla1=4 |fla1_brand=Macronix |fla1_model=MX25L3206EM2I-12G |fla1_num= |ram1=32 |ram1_brand=Nanya |ram1_model=NT5DS16M16DS-5T |ram1_num= |expansion_if_types= |expansion_usb_num= |jtag= |serial= |wi1_chip1_brand=Realtek |wi1_chip1_model=RTL8192CE |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |eth_none= |eth_cpu=true |sw_cpu=true |sw_brand= |sw_model= |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |flags= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid=TRENDnet639 |default_ssid_regex=^TRENDnet639$ |default_ip=192.168.10.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass= |oui=00:14:D1 |oui_eth=00:14:D1 }} '''300Mbps Wireless N Gigabit Router''' :[http://www.trendnet.com/asp/download_manager/list_subcategory.asp?SUBTYPE_ID=1486 Downloads] (firmware, manual, GPL source code)
"WRT-391R Rev. UB" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos and a production board. :"T003C22007A" is also silkscreened on the production board. The production board is using '''HERMEI''' and '''JACKCON''' capacitors.
The router has three antennas despite the lack of three RX/TX chains.
Two (left and middle on the FCC photos) appear to be used in a switched diversity configuration.
*The AC adapter included with the device (.. at least in the US market) is a :'''Bestec''' EA0061WAA (100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 0.5A -> 12VDC, 0.5A).
